      "content": "First, gently remove the plant from its pot to avoid damaging the delicate roots, then trim away any that appear rotten or mushy. Replace the old soil with a high-quality, well-draining houseplant potting mix, as standard garden dirt is too heavy and will suffocate the fig's roots. Finally, repot the plant using a container slightly larger than the current one and water it lightly just enough to settle the soil around the base.",
